==Location==

{{ill|Ikura|de|Ikura|ja|居倉|zh|居仓|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikura|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, {{ill|Mizuho, Gifu|en|Mizuho, Gifu|WD=Q782103|lt=Mizuho|1=Mizuho, Gifu}}, {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|en|Gifu Prefecture|WD=Q131277|lt=Gifu Prefecture|1=Gifu Prefecture}}
Surrounded by narrow winding roads; landmarks include Ikura Community Center and Nentoku-ji Temple.

==Access==

Approximately 30-minute walk from {{ill|Mieji Station|en|Mieji Station|WD=Q6843706|lt=Mieji Station|1=Mieji Station}} on the Tarumi Railway.

Take the Mizuho City community bus (Mizuho Bus) from {{ill|Hozumi Station|en|Hozumi Station|WD=Q871149|lt=Hozumi Station|1=Hozumi Station}} on the Tōkaidō Main Line and alight at Ikura Community Center.

From the intersection of Gifu Prefectural Route 92 (Gifu–Sunami–Ōno Line) at Tanokami Akamiya, travel north approximately 1.5 km.

==Other==
To the west stands the original tree of the Fuyu persimmon, one of the main varieties cultivated in the area, marked by a monument inscribed “Birthplace of the Fuyu Persimmon.”

